  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safeguard Access to Water &amp; Relocation Assistance, Solomon Islands</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help communities in remote coastal areas of the Solomon Islands who have already been impacted by the effects of climate change and rising sea levels in a manner that is culturally sensitive and protects their human rights. 

This project will aid communities in adapting to their conditions through safeguarding their access to fresh water or enabling them to relocate by providing financial assistance for building new homes. This project will also enable impacted communities to present their situation and challenges to a national forum opening conversations and ensuring their plight is at the forefront of the thoughts of government and stakeholders when developing policies relating to climate change.</narrative>
  </description>
